# Radix UI Best Practices

## Context

- Provides guidelines for Radix UI component usage
- Ensures accessibility and consistent component behavior
- Helps maintain design system consistency

## Critical Rules

- Use Radix components for accessible and customizable UI elements
- Follow the documentation for proper usage and integration
- Ensure components are styled consistently with your design system
- Utilize slots for flexible component composition
- Test components for accessibility compliance
- Import only the components you need to reduce bundle size
- Use proper ARIA attributes and keyboard navigation
- Implement proper focus management

